-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:158:    \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:245:with `output_dir = tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/natively-collected/_global_/`\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:254:[dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) per-class\nforge/docs/improve-library-coverage.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\nforge/docs/improve-library-coverage.md:9:Many already-supported libraries have low dynamic-access coverage — their\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2408:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2438:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2444:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2445:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2450:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2580:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this